  schema:name "The Ecclesial Structure of Leftist Critique: The Church as Source, Patient, and Physician of the Achievement-Subject" ;
  schema:description "The Church created the conditions Han diagnoses (mandatory confession, sacred vocation, merit theology), was the first institution to suffer their consequences (monastic acedia), and developed specific institutional treatments. Secular critique inherited the disease without the treatment." ;
